 intersection((1, 2), (2, 3)) -> \"NO\"\n- intersection((-1, 1), (0, 4)) -> \"NO\"\n- intersection((-3, -1), (-5, 5)) -> \"YES\"\n\nTo save this to /path/to/project/workspace/intersection.py on your machine, you can paste the code into that file or run:\n- mkdir -p /path/to/project/workspace\n- Then create the file with your editor of choice.\n\nIf you need an execution harness or metadata comments for a verifier, place them in a separate file to keep intersection.py containing only the function, since the request to have “only the function” while also including a harness is self-contradictory.","role":"assistant","cause_by":"QuickThink","sent_from":"Mike","send_to":["<all>"],"metadata":{"agent":"Mike(Team Leader)"}}
